{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Heat butter in a saucepan over a medium-low heat until melted. Increase temperature to a medium heat and continue cooking, watching carefully, until butter is brown and has a nutty aroma. Once browned, remove from heat and transfer to a heat-proof bowl. Leave to cool at room temperature for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, continue with recipe.","Line a baking tray with baking paper. Drop 20 portions of hazelnut chocolate spread onto prepared tray (approx. 1½-2 tsp each) then place in freezer to harden. Meanwhile, continue with recipe.","Place chocolate in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3-4 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr> until roughly chopped. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place brown sugar, caster sugar, eggs, cooled browned butter and vanilla extract in mixing bowl then mix <nobr>2 min\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Add flour, cornflour, baking powder, bicarbonate of soda and salt then mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add reserved chopped chocolate and mix <nobr>10 sec\/\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer to a large bowl, cover with cling film and place in fridge for 15 minutes.","Line 2 baking trays with baking paper and remove frozen chocolate spread drops from freezer.","Taking 2 Tbsp chilled dough at a time, shape into a disc in your palm and press a frozen chocolate spread drop into the centre. Shape cookie dough around chocolate spread drop until completely concealed, adding more dough if needed. Roll cookie into a ball and place on a prepared tray, 5 cm apart. Repeat until all chocolate spread drops and cookie dough have been used.","Freeze cookie dough balls for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 190°C.","Bake chilled cookie dough balls for 11-12 minutes (190°C) until edges are just beginning to turn golden brown.","Leave on trays to cool for 15 minutes then serve, or transfer to a wire rack to cool completely and store in an airtight container until needed."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["220 g unsalted butter, diced","280 g hazelnut chocolate spread (e.g. Nutella), or homemade equivalent","120 g milk chocolate, small pieces or callets","200 g light brown sugar","130 g caster sugar","2 medium eggs","1 ½ tsp vanilla extract","360 g plain flour","2 tsp cornflour","1 tsp baking powder","1 tsp bicarbonate of soda","1 pinch fine sea salt"]}],"id":"r296773","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-JOUrenUdw20\/XZWp2arbmyI\/AAAAAAAAfP8\/JWrU_imxH44Ylntr_TCjQ7ZT4VCiruXawCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_7YWMLs93Z5Yt4D6s.png","title":"Chocolate Lava Cookies","publishedAt":"2018-12-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4 g","fat":"16 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"42 g","calories":"1407 kJ \/ 336 kcal"},"usefulItems":"saucepan, cling film, airtight container, heat-proof bowl, large bowl, baking trays, baking paper, wire rack, hob, freezer, refrigerator, oven","basicInfo":["medium","35m","1h 40m","20 pieces"]}